        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 4:55PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 455 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Kingston, or 11 miles
east of Rome, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, nickel sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Adairsville, Kingston, Shannon, and Pinson.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
